# Shared Open-Source UI Tooling

Playwright CLI, Playwright MCP, Storybook CLI, and Chrome DevTools MCP are installed in the shared tracked bundle at `/Users/jerry/agent-orchestrator/tools/open-source-ui-tooling`, with wrappers in `/Users/jerry/.local/bin`.

- Check tool versions and update status with `/Users/jerry/agent-orchestrator/scripts/check_open_source_ui_tooling.sh`.
- Use Playwright and Chrome DevTools MCP for browser-rendered UI verification, computed style inspection, console/network checks, and screenshots.
- Use Storybook for isolated component states when a repo should own UI fixtures.
- Cursor global MCP servers are configured in `/Users/jerry/.cursor/mcp.json`; reload Cursor if the tools are not visible in a running session.
- For real project tests, prefer project-local Playwright/Storybook dependencies so CI and local runs use the repo lockfile.

## Agent and Model State

Agent and model folders are organized under `/Users/jerry/agent-orchestrator/local/agent-home`, with original home-directory paths kept as symlinks when moved. Check `/Users/jerry/agent-orchestrator/docs/AGENT_HOME_STATUS.md` before moving or assuming a path is still physical.

## Shared DeerFlow

DeerFlow is shared across Claude, Codex, Gemini, and Cursor at `/Users/jerry/agent-orchestrator/local/agent-home/deerflow/deer-flow`. Cursor's global MCP entry should use `/Users/jerry/.local/bin/agent-deerflow-mcp`; verify the gateway with `http://127.0.0.1:8001/health`.
